Luna's family had already been to two clinics before they reached the emergency hospital. By the time imaging confirmed an obstruction, they were exhausted, scared, and staring at a treatment estimate that had to be addressed before surgery could begin.

## Why this case matters

Luna is the kind of case The Wolf Project exists to support: treatable, time-sensitive, and emotionally devastating when cost becomes the gatekeeper.

## What support covers

The current goal is built around surgery, hospitalization, pain management, and the early follow-up appointments needed to make recovery realistic.

## What happens next

If the remaining deposit is covered in time, Luna can move from stabilization into active treatment without losing more time.
